o is the major factor now?</span><hr size=1> Heh Thats a loaded question.<br><br>All weapons have damage bonus's, the bonus post 40, is just higher.<br><br>In Velious/Kunark/Old Norrath, a higher damage bonus, will come from a higher delay weapon, and a weapon with same ratio, and therefor lower damage bonus will do *about* the same<br><br>However, with Luclin it is an entire different story, the insane AC values on most of these mobs cause a Large amount of the damage to be inflicted being the damage bonus, so having a large bonus, makes inflict more damage. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=50583">Madrone</a> ~ Dorfen Crusader<br><a href="http://www.winters-light.ocm">Winter's Light</a> ~ Drinal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uluthair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luthair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 1982<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/1/02 9:37:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ratio is the major factor now?</span><hr size=1> Actually Madrone with high AC what you want is DB/Delay, faster 2h still tend to be better.  (ie, a 30 delay weapon has one of 29, while a 40 delay has 34)<br><br>However the actual damage on the weapon does change min hit (DB + int(dmg/10 +0.5) ) so you need to consider that also.<br><br>Ratio is a reasonable way to compare <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> if</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> they aren't close. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6318"><img src="http://www3.sympatico.ca/lchisholm/luth_sig.jpg" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umadronedor